<subSubSection id="C32365730436FFF1FF2FFCBEFC22724F" box="[199,1001,835,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="325" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8636F80436FFF1FF2FFCBEFC22724F" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1113]" box="[199,1001,835,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0436FFF1FF2FFCBEFE83724F" bold="true" box="[199,328,835,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">Etymology</emphasis>
. From the Latin 
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0436FFF1FDEDFCBEFD89724F" box="[517,578,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">albus</emphasis>
= white, referring to the white coxae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
